hm2TrackingMib.name: hm2TrackingMib
hm2TrackingMib.contactinfo: Customer Support Postal: Hirschmann Automation and Control GmbH Stuttgarter Str. 45-51 72654 Neckartenzlingen Germany Tel: +49 7127 14 1981 Web: http://www.hicomcenter.com/ E-Mail: hicomcenter@hirschmann.com
hm2TrackingMib.description: The Hirschmann Private Tracking MIB definitions for Platform devices.

hm2TrackStatusChangeEvent.name: hm2TrackStatusChangeEvent
hm2TrackStatusChangeEvent.description: Sent when the state of a tracking instance changes between up and down.

hm2TrackingConfigTable.name: hm2TrackingConfigTable
hm2TrackingConfigTable.description: Tracking configuration table. This table provides the interface to setup a specific tracking instance in the tracking database.

hm2TrackType.name: hm2TrackType
hm2TrackType.description: The kind of an object being tracked.

hm2TrackId.name: hm2TrackId
hm2TrackId.description: The id of an object being tracked.

hm2TrackName.name: hm2TrackName
hm2TrackName.description: The name of an object being tracked.

hm2TrackDescription.name: hm2TrackDescription
hm2TrackDescription.description: The name of an object being tracked.

hm2TrackOperState.name: hm2TrackOperState
hm2TrackOperState.description: Shows if the tracked object is currently up(1), down(2) or notReady(3). in case the state indicates notReady, the corresponding configuration is missing or invalid.

hm2TrackNumberOfChanges.name: hm2TrackNumberOfChanges
hm2TrackNumberOfChanges.description: The number of state changes after an object being tracked, entered its operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

hm2TrackTimeLastChange.name: hm2TrackTimeLastChange
hm2TrackTimeLastChange.description: The time of the last state change of an object being tracked, measured in seconds since 00:00:00, January 1, 1970. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains the time the system was re-initialized. value.

hm2TrackSendStateChangeTrap.name: hm2TrackSendStateChangeTrap
hm2TrackSendStateChangeTrap.description: Enables or disables the sending of a trap when hm2TrackStatus changes

hm2TrackStatus.name: hm2TrackStatus
hm2TrackStatus.description: Defines the status of the tracking database entry. Set to createAndWait(5) to create a new row. Set to destroy(6) to delete an entry. Reads as active(1) if the tracked object exists and is trackable, notReady(3) otherwise.

hm2TrackingInterfaceTable.name: hm2TrackingInterfaceTable
hm2TrackingInterfaceTable.description: Interface tracking configuration table. This table provides the interface to setup the parameters for an interface tracking object.

hm2TrackInterfaceId.name: hm2TrackInterfaceId
hm2TrackInterfaceId.description: The identifier of the interface object being tracked.

hm2TrackIfNumber.name: hm2TrackIfNumber
hm2TrackIfNumber.description: The number of the interface being tracked.

hm2TrackIfLinkUpDelay.name: hm2TrackIfLinkUpDelay
hm2TrackIfLinkUpDelay.description: If a link-up recovers within this delay, the tracked object is not considered as up.

hm2TrackIfLinkDownDelay.name: hm2TrackIfLinkDownDelay
hm2TrackIfLinkDownDelay.description: If a link-down recovers within this delay, the tracked object is not considered as down.

hm2TrackingPingTable.name: hm2TrackingPingTable
hm2TrackingPingTable.description: Ping tracking configuration table. This table provides the interface to setup the parameters for a ping tracking object.

hm2TrackPingId.name: hm2TrackPingId
hm2TrackPingId.description: The identifier of the ping object being tracked.

hm2TrackPingIfNumber.name: hm2TrackPingIfNumber
hm2TrackPingIfNumber.description: The number of the source interface, the ping packets are sent. A value of Zero (0) indicates that no interface is configured.

hm2TrackPingInetAddrType.name: hm2TrackPingInetAddrType
hm2TrackPingInetAddrType.description: The address type of the router being monitored.

hm2TrackPingInetAddr.name: hm2TrackPingInetAddr
hm2TrackPingInetAddr.description: The address of the router being monitored.

hm2TrackPingInterval.name: hm2TrackPingInterval
hm2TrackPingInterval.description: The number of milliseconds between the pings to the target router address.

hm2TrackPingMiss.name: hm2TrackPingMiss
hm2TrackPingMiss.description: This specifies the number of consecutive ping misses until the tracked object is considered to be down.

hm2TrackPingSuccess.name: hm2TrackPingSuccess
hm2TrackPingSuccess.description: This specifies the number of consecutive ping successes until the tracked object is considered to be up.

hm2TrackPingTimeout.name: hm2TrackPingTimeout
hm2TrackPingTimeout.description: This specifies the timeout in milliseconds for a ping reply. After the timeout the ping reply is considered as lost.

hm2TrackPingTTL.name: hm2TrackPingTTL
hm2TrackPingTTL.description: This specifies the time to live for a ping request packet.

hm2TrackPingBestRouteIfNumber.name: hm2TrackPingBestRouteIfNumber
hm2TrackPingBestRouteIfNumber.description: This shows the number of the interface which belongs to the best route. The interface number is zero if the best route is not used to send ping packets.

hm2TrackLogicalInstanceTable.name: hm2TrackLogicalInstanceTable
hm2TrackLogicalInstanceTable.description: This table contains the configuration of the tracking instances that are combined into logical tracking instances.

hm2TrackLogicalId.name: hm2TrackLogicalId
hm2TrackLogicalId.description: The identifier of the logical object being tracked.

hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameA.name: hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameA
hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameA.description: The name of the tracking object to be used as operand A in the logical operation: A operator B.

hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameB.name: hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameB
hm2TrackLogicalOperandNameB.description: The name of the tracking object to be used as operand B in the logical operation: A operator B.

hm2TrackLogicalOperator.name: hm2TrackLogicalOperator
hm2TrackLogicalOperator.description: Defines the logical operation performed on the configured operands A and B.

hm2TrackingApplicationTable.name: hm2TrackingApplicationTable
hm2TrackingApplicationTable.description: This table contains information about registered applications, for each object being tracked.

hm2TrackAppId.name: hm2TrackAppId
hm2TrackAppId.description: The id of an application which tracks an object.

hm2TrackAppName.name: hm2TrackAppName
hm2TrackAppName.description: The name of the registered application.

hm2TrackAppObjectName.name: hm2TrackAppObjectName
hm2TrackAppObjectName.description: The name of the tracking object the application registered for.

hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackId.name: hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackId
hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackId.description: Associate and dissociate the tracking instance to a static route. To dissociate, pass an empty string.

hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackState.name: hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackState
hm2TrackStaticRouteTrackState.description: Shows if the tracked object is currently up(1), down(2) or notReady(3). in case the state indicates notReady, the corresponding configuration is missing or invalid.
